Hi, got the following information 

1. Number of Sessions: Approximately 5 sessions are planned, but this is flexible depending on the need. If there are multiple performances, the choreography can be completed within 2-3 sessions, with the remaining sessions dedicated to revisions and polishing.

2. Timings of Studio Sessions: The session timings are completely flexible and can be adjusted to suit your schedule, especially considering the wedding preparations. While there are some constraints on weekday evenings, we are open to accommodating your preferred time slots.

3. At-Home Dance Prep for Family Members: Yes, the choreographer will visit your place to help the rest of the family members with their dance preparations.

4. Charges for Longer Performances: There is no distinction between solo, duet, or group performances. The charges are based purely on the duration of the performance. For every additional minute, the cost is ₹1,000 per minute.

5. Charges for Solo Performances: As mentioned, there are no separate charges for solo performances. The pricing is entirely time-based, irrespective of whether it's a solo, duet, or group performance.

text_body: Thanks. I will check this out.

While I check this out, need help in figuring out the phillipines Visa (I have a US visa so need to check if I need it separately or not). Moreover, I got to know getting Singapore visa is easier and it allows entry to phillipines. 

Can you help me get all the details ?
Also, checklist of required documents for the visa
Sure, let us check and get back.
Thanks! :)

Hi Anish,
As per the Philippine Embassy website, No visa is needed for Indian passport holders visiting for tourism, staying up to 14 days, and having a valid visa or permanent residency from the U.S., U.K., Canada, Australia, Japan, Singapore, or a Schengen country.
- Requirements: Passport valid for 6 months, return/onward ticket, and no immigration issues in the Philippines.

*Visa Application Requirements*
1. Notarized application form.  
2. Passport (valid for at least 6 months) + one photocopy of data page.  
3. Proof of ticket reservation.  
4. One 2” x 2” colored photo (white background).  
5. Proof of financial capacity (bank statement or employment certificate).  
6. Self-addressed prepaid return envelope (USPS Priority Mail).  
7. Visa fee ($30 or $40 via money order).  
8. Proof of COVID-19 vaccination.

{"url": "https://getbyferry.com/en-us/coron-el-nido", "body": "Hi Anish, please find the response to your questions below:

*Travel from Busuanga Airport to Paolyn Houseboats in Coron*
Paolyn Houseboats offers complimentary transfers from Busuanga Airport (USU) to their location. Upon arrival at the airport, their staff will assist you with the transfer, which includes a van ride to Coron Town (approximately 30 minutes) followed by a speedboat journey to the houseboats (around 15 minutes). The total transfer time is approximately 45 minutes

*Travel from Coron to El Nido*
There are three primary options for traveling from Coron to El Nido:
1. Fast Ferry: This is the most popular method. The journey takes approximately 3.5 to 5 hours, depending on sea conditions. Ferries typically depart from Coron Pier in the morning, around 7:00 AM, and arrive at El Nido Ferry Terminal by midday. Ticket prices range from $47 to $54 per person. - https://getbyferry.com/en-us/coron-el-nido

2. Flights -   This is the most fastest method that takes only 40 minutes from Coron to El Nido, There are only two flights, one departs at 9:50 am and and the other at 11:55 am. This is costing $87 per person - https://booking.air-swift.com/vars/public/b/FlightCal.aspx?VARSSessionID=c2e1eacf-b42d-40e4-b108-0cd97f823c8e

3. Tourist Ferry: A more leisurely option, these ferries take about 5 to 6 hours to reach El Nido. They usually depart Coron Port in the morning and arrive in the afternoon. Ticket prices are generally lower than the fast ferry, but specific rates can vary. - https://www.bookaway.com/routes/philippines/coron-to-el-nido

*Travel from El Nido to Puerto Princesa*
1. Bus/Minivan - Buses operate between El Nido and Puerto Princesa, with a travel time of approximately 5 to 6 hours. These cost starting from $11 - https://www.rome2rio.com/map/El-Nido/Port-of-Puerto-Princesa#trips

2. Private Van: For a more comfortable and flexible option, private van transfers are available. The travel time is similar to that of shared minivans, but the cost is higher.
